@description.body: Fired when the flash object still is loading. The loading action can be prevented by calling {@link qx.event.type.Event#preventDefault} on the event object

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the DOM element of the Flash movie. Note: If you call the method before the widget is rendered, it will always return null. Therefore call the method after the {@link #appear} event is fired.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {Element|null} The DOM element of the Flash movie.
@return.description: The DOM element of the Flash movie.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Checks if the movie is loaded.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {Boolean} true When the movie is completely loaded, otherwise false.
@return.description: true When the movie is completely loaded, otherwise false.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Returns the current loaded state from the Flash movie.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: overridden

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Checks the current loaded state and fires one of the defined events: {@link #loading}, {@link #loaded} or {@link #timeout}. Note the {@link #timeout} event is fired when the check reached the defined {@link #loadTimeout}.
